channel.title: Computer had fatal disk error had to replace harddrive, so I've got a question
channel.description:
Alright well as aforementioned, my computer has been wiped clean. So, it looks like I'm starting a new project.
And I've come here to ask what to do.
What deob? 317, 474, 508, etc.
What base? (I would like one that is clean with no features if possible)

item.title: Computer had fatal disk error had to replace harddrive, so I've got a question
item.dc:creator: @kihomura Kihomura
item.description:
@kihomura wrote:

Use the word “deob” correctly. Obfuscation is making code hard to read to stop people from fucking with it. Deobfuscation is the opposite.

Read full topic

item.title: Computer had fatal disk error had to replace harddrive, so I've got a question
item.dc:creator: @n10si_t n10si t
item.description:
@n10si_t wrote:

[quote=“rain1994, post:2, topic:347751”]Deob i don’t know what it means… srry a 317 is what most people use as a source but more and more people are moving to a 508 wich is the “newer version of rs” 47s is right in between them, has skill capes,emotes, and gwd.

Now i take it your are new to coding? you might not want to start with a “base” you will probably want to start out with a source that already has features that you can just edit and what not.

But here is the link to a “base”(clean no features) http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,441338.msg3241863.html#msg3241863

Good luck[/quote]

No, I’m not that new, been doing this for a year or so.

And that base didn’t work for me. Like literally didn’t work.

Read full topic
